<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="146" type="collection and habitat data">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Collection and habitat data.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
<taxonomicName authority="C.G.Thomson, 1859" authorityName="C.G.Thomson" authorityYear="1859" class="Insecta" family="Trogossitidae" genus="Calitys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calitys scabra" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scabra">Calitys scabra</taxonomicName>
was captured in Lindgren funnel traps deployed in an old red oak forest, a mature red spruce stand, an old-growth red pine forest, and an old mixed forest. This species was reported from under bark of dead pine and from 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Fomitopsidaceae" genus="Fomitopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Fomitopsis pinicola" order="Polyporales" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="pinicola">Fomitopsis pinicola</taxonomicName>
(Fr.) Kar. (
<bibRefCitation author="Barron, JR" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada" pageId="11" pageNumber="152" pagination="1 - 143" title="A revision of the Trogossitidae of America north of Mexico." url="10.4039/entm10375fv" volume="75" year="1971">Barron 1971</bibRefCitation>
). Adults were collected during May, June, and July.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="146" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Distribution in Canada and Alaska.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
AK, NT, BC, AB, MB, ON, QC, NB, NS (
<bibRefCitation pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Bousquet 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Majka, CG" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Acadian Entomological Society" pageId="11" pageNumber="152" pagination="25 - 31" title="The Trogossitidae (Coleoptera) of Atlantic Canada." volume="7" year="2011">Majka 2011</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Majka, CG" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Acadian Entomological Society" pageId="11" pageNumber="152" pagination="25 - 31" title="The Trogossitidae (Coleoptera) of Atlantic Canada." volume="7" year="2011">Majka (2011)</bibRefCitation>
reported this Holarctic species for the first time from New Brunswick based on a specimen collected by W. McIntosh in Saint John, ca. 1900. The above records are the first recent records of this species for New Brunswick.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
